ygData.messageBody:
Just to clarify, the vast majority of these machines are built by the person
doing the overclocking. These are not pre-built machines, eg: Not Gateway,
Dell, etc. These processors are going from factory, to vendor, to user. :)

Atonal

Ram - th e results for me...)


Nah, more bang for the buck...consider also, any pc builder worth their salt
will have filtered the bad processors out before you ever get to see the
machines, i.e. doa rate and failure rate are gonna be much lower than the
builders.
